  "response_text": "# Healthy Meal Prep Plan (1 Week)\n\n## Sunday Prep Tasks\n- Shop for ingredients\n- Wash & chop vegetables\n- Cook grains and proteins\n- Portion into containers\n\n---\n\n## BREAKFAST OPTIONS\n\n**Overnight Oats** (5 servings)\n- Rolled oats, Greek yogurt, almond milk, berries, honey\n- Prep: Mix in jars, refrigerate\n\n**Veggie Egg Muffins** (12 pieces)\n- Eggs, spinach, bell peppers, cheese\n- Bake at 350°F for 20 minutes\n\n---\n\n## LUNCH BOWLS (3 varieties)\n\n**Mediterranean Bowl**\n- Quinoa base\n- Grilled chicken, cucumber, tomatoes, feta, olives\n- Lemon-olive oil dressing\n\n**Asian Buddha Bowl**\n- Brown rice base\n- Baked tofu, broccoli, carrots, edamame\n- Ginger-sesame dressing\n\n**Southwest Grain Bowl**\n- Black beans, corn, brown rice\n- Lean ground turkey, bell peppers\n- Cilantro-lime dressing\n\n---\n\n## SNACKS\n\n- Greek yogurt with granola\n- Hummus with carrot/celery sticks\n- Mixed nuts (1 oz portions)\n- Fresh fruit\n- Cheese & whole grain crackers\n\n---\n\n## DINNER (2 proteins)\n\n**Baked Salmon** with roasted vegetables\n**Lean Ground Turkey** with whole wheat pasta and marinara\n\n---\n\n## TIPS\n✓ Use glass containers (microwave-safe)\n✓ Store dressings separately\n✓ Label with dates\n✓ Meals stay fresh 3-4 days\n\nWould you like specific recipes or a shopping list?",
